{%- comment -%}
  Single accordion item (spec §5.4), built on native <details>/<summary> rather
  than a fully custom ARIA widget — the browser already provides correct
  expand/collapse semantics, keyboard support (Enter/Space on summary), and state
  announcement for free, and the markup still works with zero JS (instant
  open/close, no animation). assets/accordion.js progressively enhances any
  <accordion-group> wrapping one or more of these with the animated open/close and
  optional one-open-at-a-time behavior.

  The "+" glyph rotates 45° into a close "×" via CSS on [open] — one icon, not two.

  Accepts:
  - title (required), content (required, captured HTML)
  - open (bool): renders already expanded
  - id: optional, for deep-linking (#faq-shipping etc.)
{%- endcomment -%}
<details class="accordion-item"{% if open %} open{% endif %}{% if id %} id="{{ id }}"{% endif %}>
  <summary class="accordion-item__header">
    <span class="accordion-item__title">{{ title }}</span>
    <span class="accordion-item__icon">{% render 'icon', name: 'plus' %}</span>
  </summary>
  <div class="accordion-item__panel">
    <div class="accordion-item__panel-inner prose">{{ content }}</div>
  </div>
</details>
